# Ponytail Coding Rules

- Always question whether code needs to exist at all (YAGNI).
- Reuse existing codebase helpers, utils, and patterns.
- Prefer standard library and native language/platform features before custom code or new dependencies.
- Write the minimum amount of code that works reliably.
- No unrequested abstractions, boilerplate, or speculative scaffolding.
